* East Tennessee Writers Hall of Fame (2019)
* [[Grammy Hall of Fame]] – "Coat of Many Colors – 1971 Recording" (2019)<ref>{{cite web|title=Grammy Hall of Fame Inductees|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/hall-of-fame#c|website=Grammy.org|date=October 18, 2010|access-date=March 30, 2021}}</ref>

In 2022, she was nominated for induction into the [[Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]].<ref>{{cite magazine | last=Freeman | first=Jon | title=Why Dolly Parton Damn Sure Belongs in the Rock & Roll Hall of Fame, Y'all | magazine=Rolling Stone | date=2022-02-02 | url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-country/dolly-parton-rock-and-roll-hall-of-fame-1294186/ | access-date=2022-02-03}}</ref> Parton declined the nomination in March 2022, believing that the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame was "for the people in [[rock music]]".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Colarossi |first=Natalie |date=2022-03-14 |title=Why Dolly Parton rejected Rock and Roll Hall of Fame nomination |url=https://www.newsweek.com/why-dolly-parton-rejected-rock-roll-hall-fame-nomination-1687776 |access-date=2022-03-14 |website=Newsweek |language=en}}</ref><ref name="Reason">{{cite web |title='Dreams do still come true' in a new novel by Dolly Parton and James Patterson |url=https://www.npr.org/2022/04/29/1095444447/dolly-parton-james-patterson-novel |website=NPR.org |access-date=29 April 2022 |language=en}}</ref> In April 2022, after learning that she was mistaken, Parton said she would accept her induction if she were chosen for the honor.<ref name="Reason"/> In May 2022, the Rock and Roll Hall of the Fame announced that she would indeed be inducted.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Arnold |first=Chuck |date=2022-05-04 |title=Rock & Roll Hall of Fame inducts Dolly Parton against her wishes |url=https://nypost.com/2022/05/04/rock-roll-hall-of-fame-inducts-dolly-parton-against-her-wishes/ |access-date=2022-05-04 |website=New York Post}}</ref>

